data.current_summary: Deletes an event template for the app
data.current_description:
This will delete the event template. All associated events will be removed from search results and the timeline UI.

This action can't be undone, so it's highly recommended that you stop using any associated events before deleting a template.
data.summary_suggestion: Archive an event template and remove associated events
data.description_suggestion: Permanently deletes an event template and all associated timeline events. Deleted events will be removed from search results and no longer appear in timeline UI for any CRM objects. This action is irreversible. All events created using this template will be deleted. It is strongly recommended to stop creating events with this template and verify no active dependencies before executing this operation.

data.current_summary: Adds a token to an existing event template
data.current_description:
Once you've defined an event template, it's likely that you'll want to define tokens for it as well. You can do this on the event template itself or update individual tokens here.

Event type tokens allow you to attach custom data to events displayed in a timeline or used for list segmentation.
 
You can also use `objectPropertyName` to associate any CRM object properties. This will allow you to fully build out CRM objects.

Token names should be unique across the template.
data.description_suggestion: Adds a new token to an existing event template. Tokens define custom data fields that can be populated when creating timeline events. Each token can be mapped to CRM object properties via the `objectPropertyName` field to automatically populate contact, company, ticket, or deal data. Token names must be unique within the template. Returns the created token definition. Tokens can be used for event display in timelines and for list segmentation.
data.reasoning: Summary is clear and action-oriented. Description is somewhat disorganized and lacks clarity about what is returned. data.current_summary: Removes a token from the event template
data.current_description:
This will remove the token from an existing template. Existing events and CRM objects will still retain the token and its mapped object properties, but new ones will not.

The timeline will still display this property for older CRM objects if it's still referenced in the template `Markdown`. New events will not.

Any lists or reports referencing deleted tokens will no longer return new contacts, but old ones will still exist in the lists.
data.description_suggestion: Archives a token from an event template, preventing it from being used in new events. Existing events and CRM objects retain the archived token and its mapped properties. The timeline will continue displaying the token for existing CRM objects if referenced in the template Markdown, but new events will not include it. Lists and reports referencing the archived token will exclude new records but retain existing ones. Returns a 204 No Content response on success.
data.reasoning: Summary uses 'Removes' which is vague about the archival nature. Description is verbose and unclear about the return value.
